The evidence with the title 'Bill Clinton: Gingrich opposed bill that led to balanced budgets ... ' says Dec 20, 2011  ... They examined Gingrich 's claim that, “ for four years, we balanced the budget and paid off $ 405 billion in debt, ” and declared the statement false. The first two budgets that were created when Gingrich was speaker – for fiscal 1996 and 1997 – did not balance . The next two years, there was a surplus. 
